.SH "NAME"
irq_set_irq_wake \- control irq power management wakeup
.SH "SYNOPSIS"
.HP \w'int\ irq_set_irq_wake('u
.BI "int irq_set_irq_wake(unsigned\ int\ " "irq" ", unsigned\ int\ " "on" ");"
.SH "ARGUMENTS"
.PP
\fIirq\fR
.RS 4
interrupt to control
.RE
.PP
\fIon\fR
.RS 4
enable/disable power management wakeup
.RE
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
.PP
Enable/disable power management wakeup mode, which is disabled by default\&. Enables and disables must match, just as they match for non\-wakeup mode support\&.
.PP
Wakeup mode lets this IRQ wake the system from sleep states like
\(lqsuspend to RAM\(rq\&.
